content.raw:
When I looked at the test, the order of arguments confused me (`Set(const value, destination)`), probably because I am used to the [msgs::Set](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/cd76df23c3519da47aaf4a283b1ba1a9d718c6c0/gazebo/msgs/msgs.hh#msgs.hh-314) functions which have a pattern of `Set(destination, const value)`.

What do you think about reversing the order of these arguments?
content.html:
When I looked at the test, the order of arguments confused me (Set(const value, destination)), probably because I am used to the msgs::Set functions which have a pattern of Set(destination, const value).

What do you think about reversing the order of these arguments?
